<br>
It appears that there are levels of threateningly, and here is the evidence I've collected to support this.<br>
<br>
My wife's first character was a wood elf warrior that followed Rallos Zek. Myself and some friends took her to Kaladim to PL her with some CB belts. We were standing outside the gates in Butcher Block close to the guards. After about 10 seconds of just standing there chatting, one of the guards just ran over and smacked my wife's character, obviously killing her. I then did my own research and found that followers of Rallos Zek con &quot;threateningly&quot; to the dorf guards.<br>
<br>
When I was busy working faction up with the Warrior Guild in Qeynos, I was turning in belts to the &quot;good&quot; warrior guild in Freeport. This caused me to loss faction with the Freeport Militia. I noticed that over time, the agro radius of the guards, while I was conning &quot;threateningly&quot;, got bigger. <br>
<br>
For example, and these are made up numbers, the radius increased in increments(sp?) of 5 feet. Everytime I turned in more belts, the guards seemed to agro while I was at a further distance than the time before.<br>
<br>
This lead me to believe that there are levels to the &quot;threateningly&quot; con you get from mobs.<br>
<br>
But then again, I might be wrong.<br>
